<kml>
<concept name=Medium>
<system-documentation name=Medium>
<gpd-documentation name=Roles>


<superconcept name=Role>

  <definition>
    Medium is the <conceptref name=Role> played by an Entity which is
    the <slot>base</slot> of a <conceptref name=Express> or a <conceptref name=Interpret>.
  </definition>

<requiredslotlist>
   <slotdescription name=played-by>
     the Communication-Entity that's playing the role of medium
   </slotdescription>
   <slotdescription name=in-event>
     the <conceptref name=Action> event that the Entity is engaged in
   </slotdescription>

</requiredslotlist>

<examplesentencelist>

  <examplesentence>
     <text>The president told him about the war.</text>
     <comment>
     In this example, the Medium role is described with these properties:
     </comment>
     <slotdescription name=in-event><conceptref name=Express> with
         <slot>object</slot>= Is the <conceptref name=Information> which in this example is the information about the war.
</slotdescription> and the <slot> agent </slot> = The preseident.
     <slotdescription name=played-by> speech (spoken language) </slotdescription> as the <slot> base-of </slot> the <conceptref name=Express>
  </examplesentence>

</examplesentencelist>

</kml>

